5) Audio limit vs transcription

They’re different pipelines.
	•	Audio input (voice) → has duration limits (e.g., ~10 min) for processing/latency/cost reasons
	•	Text input (typed or transcribed) → goes through the normal text system, which can handle longer content

So:

The limit is on audio processing, not on text understanding

That’s why you can still transcribe and send it.

